<br>
Recently I wrote an event calendar application for the EQ guild I belong to,  and while I was writing this thing, I realized it would be much more useful if it were integrated with our message board. For example, you could post messages asking questions about the event, or provide some feedback after it was over.  <br>
<br>
This got me thinking:  as far as I know, there isn’t an integrated package of web applications out there specifically for online gaming groups like VS.  Most groups use some combination of homegrown pages, some message board they found (like EZ board), ICQ and/or possibly a chat plug-in on their site.<br>
<br>
So I’d like to create something specifically for gamers to build communities on the web.  For example, it should include message boards, news, a member database, an event calendar, polls & elections, a library/gallery, and hopefully whatever else people might find useful.  <br>
<br>
Before I get started on designing pages or writing code, you can help by providing input to make sure that what I design will meet the needs of people in the online gaming community.  So I've created a survey for anyone with the time to answer a few questions.<br>
<br>
This isn’t a scientific study.  I’ll be using the responses to develop personas that represent the target audience. (That would be all of you…) Personas are useful because they make it easier to avoid the pitfall of designing software just for <I>me</I>, since my preferences may not represent the community overall.<br>
<br>
While I cannot guarantee results or schedules, I hope to release something in several months, and to make the product available for free with open source.  I hope this will be my way of giving back to the online gaming community.<br>
<br>
Your answers to the survey are saved on my computer, but no information that could be used to identify you is saved unless you provide such information yourself.  Thanks in advance to anyone who has time to participate!<br>
<br>
